  "text": "The `acks` producer configuration value propagates through the Kafka codebase following this chain:\n\n1. **Configuration Definition** (ProducerConfig.java): The ACKS_CONFIG constant is defined at line 123. The parseAcks method (line 639-643) validates the acks value, accepting 'all' (converted to -1), '0', or '1'. During producer initialization (line 579-602), the acks value is validated to ensure compatibility with idempotent producers.\n\n2. **Client-Side Initialization** (KafkaProducer.java): In the newSender method (line 525), the acks value is read from ProducerConfig using `producerConfig.getString(ProducerConfig.ACKS_CONFIG)` and parsed as a short integer, then passed to the Sender constructor.\n\n3. **Request Construction** (Sender.java): The Sender class stores the acks value as a field (line 99, 148). In the sendProduceRequest method (line 864-920), the acks value is encoded into the ProduceRequestData via `.setAcks(acks)` at line 897.\n\n4. **Protocol Encoding** (ProduceRequest.java and ProduceRequest.json): The ProduceRequest class encodes the acks field (line 91, 104) from the ProduceRequestData. The protocol definition (ProduceRequest.json line 55-56) specifies that 'Acks' is an int16 field with values: 0 (no acknowledgments), 1 (leader only), or -1 (full ISR).\n\n5. **Broker-Side Request Handling** (KafkaApis.scala): The handleProduceRequest method (line 388) processes the incoming ProduceRequest and checks the acks value to determine request quota enforcement (line 481-486) and response handling (line 499-520). The requiredAcks value is passed to ReplicaManager.handleProduceAppend at line 537.\n\n6. **Replica Management** (ReplicaManager.scala): The handleProduceAppend method (line 731-748) receives the requiredAcks parameter and creates a DelayedProduce operation (line 918-919) with the produce metadata. It determines whether acknowledgments are required by calling partition.appendRecordsToLeader at line 1408.\n\n7. **Broker-Side Acknowledgment Logic** (Partition.scala): The appendRecordsToLeader method (line 1361-1375) checks if the ISR size meets the minimum ISR requirement when requiredAcks == -1 (acks=all). The checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset method (line 1089-1123) verifies that enough replicas have reached the required offset by checking the high watermark and in-sync replicas.\n\n8. **Delayed Operation Management** (DelayedProduce.scala): The ProduceMetadata class (line 43) stores the produceRequiredAcks value. The DelayedProduce operation (line 57-135) monitors partition acknowledgment status via the tryComplete method (line 89-117), which checks if enough replicas have acknowledged the write using partition.checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset."
}

